(7, 1, 'Homework Assistance', 'logo_1435307738054.jpg', 'cover_1434289289213.png', 'The homework assistance is a place for children and youth that have another first language than Swedish. For IM homework assistance is more than just help with the homework. Its about offering a space where people, who usually don’t meet, can meet. <br><br>Mondays 17.00 - 18.45 at Tensta bibliotek<br>Wednesdays 16.30 - 18.30 at Tensta konsthall<br>', 'Homework Assistance: Tensta', '<br>', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-tensta', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:35:38'),
(8, 0, 'Crossroads', 'logo_1435259434903.png', '', '<div><br></div>Crossroads is an advice and support network for people from European countries that live in poverty and/or are homeless in Stockholm<br><br>Crossroads can offer individual action plans, different courses, information about Swedish society and also food, a warm place and a place to rest. <br><br>Crossroads work for EU-migrants, foreign EU-citizens and citizens from countries outside of the EU that have a permanent visa from another EU-country. We call our staff EU- counsellors and we offer individual action-plans, help to get in contact with Swedish and European organisations and authorities, employers, housing opportunities and caretakers.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Contact:</span><br>Krukmakargatan 36A<br>118 51 Stockholm<br><br>Tel: 08-68 42 3150<br>crossroads@stadsmissionen.se<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Open hours:</span><br><div>Drop in<br>Monday-Friday 8:00-12:00<br><br>Schedules call and group-activities <br>Mondays-Thursdays 12.30-15.30<br><br>Visitors can get information about their rights and obligations as EU-citizens in Sweden and are offered free lunch, shower, possibility to do laundry and change clothes. <br><div><br></div><div>Crossroads is run and financed by Stockholms Stadsmission in collaboration with Arbetsförmedlingen, Europeiska Socialfonden, Frälsningsarmén and the city of Stockholm. Citykyrkan, Läkare i världen, Ny Gemenskap, Röda Korset och S:ta Clara church also collaborate with the project.<br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända. </span><br></div></div>', 'Information and support for EU-citizens/migrants.', 'Crossroads is an advice and support network for people from European countries that live in poverty and/or are homeless in Stockholm.&nbsp;<div><br></div>', 'http://stockholmcrossroads.se/', 'crossroads@stadsmissionen.se', 'en', 38, 1, '2015-09-29 18:18:18'),
(9, 1, 'Homework Assistance: Hässelby', 'logo_1435307634771.png', 'cover_1434289192377.png', 'Hässelby:  Mondays and tuesdays 17.00-18.45 at Hässelby gårds lärandecenter.<br><br>IMs homework assistance in Hässelby is a space for children from two schools in Hässelby Gård, where more than 40 languages are spoken. Many or the children recently came to sweden, has another mothertongue than Swedish and few have the possibility to get help with homework at home.<br>', 'Homework Assistance: Hässelby', '<br>', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-hasselby', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:33:54'),
(10, 0, 'Invitationsdepartementet', 'logo_1449655657182.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/invitationsdepartementet?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Invitationsdepartementet</span></div>Invitationsdepartementet ("United Invitations") is about food, language and social interactions. <br><br>It’s about making memorable meals and new dinner constellations happen. <br><br>The meal takes place with no strings attached, and signing up includes no obligations apart from serving food at the agreed time. <br><br>At least one of the participants should be a person who has moved to this country from a different country. The guest is always welcomed to bring one person along to the dinner.&nbsp;<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Visit their website to read more!&nbsp;<a href="http://invitationsdepartementet.eu/">http://invitationsdepartementet.eu/</a><br><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Note: The meal is a dinner, free of charge, and in someone’s home.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-style: italic;">Host and guests participate out of their own free will and with responsibility for themselves.</span></div></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Invite a stranger home for dinner!<br>', 'Invitationsdepartementet helps you invite somebody, or be invited by somebody, home for dinner. It''s a fun way for new and established Swedes to meet!<br><br><br>', 'http://invitationsdepartementet.eu/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 12:07:37'),
(11, 0, 'Kompisbyrån', 'logo_1441367263896.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/kompisbyran?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Kompisbyrån</span></div>The primary goal of Kompisbyrån is for newcomers to improve their Swedish.<br><br>Therefore, they match people who want to practice their Swedish with people who want to help somebody improve their Swedish. A “Kompisfika” is a cultural exchange over a cup of coffee of people with different backgrounds, experiences, interests and ages. <br><br>A “fika” is a central element of Swedish culture and is associated with a nice, relaxing and fun meeting. If you want to practice your Swedish over a “fika”, please contact them by filling out the form on the startpage on their website! <br><br><a href="http://kompisbyran.se/" style="font-weight: normal;">Kompisbyrån Website </a><br><a href="https://www.facebook.com/kompisbyran/info?tab=page_info" style="font-weight: normal;">Facebook Link</a><div><br></div><div><br><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'Meet new friends, speak Swedish and learn new things over a "fika"!', 'Kompisbyrån matches people who want to practice their Swedish with people who want to help somebody improve their Swedish. <br><div><br></div>', 'http://kompisbyran.se/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 11:43:12'),
(12, 0, 'Terrafem', 'logo_1434272348557.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/terrafem?fref=ts', '<span style="font-weight: bold;">Terrafem</span><div>Terrafem is an organisation working for you who have been or are battered, raped, harassed, threatened, in risk of forced marriage, repressed in your personal life or in some other way experience abuse by your husband, partner, boyfriend, father, brother or some other person.<br><br>Terrafem is a non-profit organisation that works for the right of women of all ages to live in a society without the violence and abuse of men.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Terrafem runs</span><span style="font-weight: normal;"> </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">Sweden''s only national helpline for immigrant women of all ages</span>. The helpline (020-52 10 10) offers support in about 45 languages.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Terrafem also gives legal advice and offers a women''s shelter, a shelter for girls and apartments with daily support.</span><br><br>They will talk to you over the phone or make plans for you to visit them for a private meeting.<br><br>The people who work at Terrafem have vast experience of supporting women and girls who have been abused.<br><br>Neither your husband, partner, boyfriend, father, brother nor any other man has the right to beat you. It''s not your fault. The man is responsible for his actions.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">You can contact them on our national helpline 020-52 10 10.&nbsp;</span>Your call is free of charge. Your call will not be listed on your phone bill. You can call from a pay phone, a listed telephone or a mobile. You can remain anonymous in your contact with Terrafem.<br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Visit their website:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.terrafem.org">http://www.terrafem.org</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'Helpline in 45 languages and shelters for girls and women.', 'Terrafem is a non-profit organisation that works for the right of women of all ages to live in a society without the violence and abuse of men.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>They offer a national helpline for immigrant women of all ages, legal advice, shelters for women and girls, apartments with daily support.&nbsp;</div>', 'http://www.terrafem.org', '', 'en', 29, 1, '2015-09-29 18:06:58'),
(13, 0, 'HEM, association for homeless EU-migrants', 'logo_1435313446035.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/organisationhem?fref=ts', '<div><br></div>HEM works for the rights of EU-citizens/migrants and assists with the following:&nbsp;<div><ul><li>emergency housing solutions such as moving a camp</li><li>translation and interpretation, for example when visiting authorities</li><li>Swedish lessons - HEM teaches three different levels depending on entry level</li></ul>Once a week a translator from the network will be available to join visits to Doctors of the World (Läkare i världen) and assist with language barriers.&nbsp;<br><br>Sometimes it is necessary to visit authorities such as the social services. Maybe you need urgent help to organise a trip home if for example someone in your family has become ill.&nbsp;</div><div><br>They also accompany people to Arbetsförmedlingen (the Swedish Public Employment Services) to apply for a co-ordination number so that those that are offered the opportunity to work can do so.&nbsp;</div><div><br>They can also help with translation over phone.</div><div><br></div><div>For contact:&nbsp;</div><div>info@foreningenhem.se</div><div>http://foreningenhem.se</div><div>0728-704 704</div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">https://www.facebook.com/organisationhem<br><br>Text written by Stan för nyanlända.<br></span></div>', 'Association that offers practical support to EU-migrants.', 'HEM works for the rights of EU-migrants and offers different kinds of practical support and Swedish lessons.<div><br></div>', 'http://foreningenhem.se', 'info@foreningenhem.se', 'en', 41, 1, '2015-09-29 18:07:29'),
(15, 1, 'Homework assistance ', 'logo_1435307193566.png', 'cover_1434289691755.png', 'Kista Bibliotek with the Red Cross and Mattecentrum<br><br>Do you need assistance with your homework? Come and get help from volunteers from the Red Cross and Mattecentrum.<br><br>Every Thursday between 17.00 and 19.00 our talented homework helpers are stationed in the library.<br><br>It is a free service and you don’t have to sign up before- Welcome!<br><br>Website <br><br>(on Mondays Kista Galaxy also offers homework assistance 17.00-19.00 in the library)', 'Homework Assistance Kista Bibliotek<br>', '<br>', '', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:26:33'),
(16, 1, 'Handicraft and Swedish ', 'logo_1435306668176.jpg', '', 'Do you like to embroider, knit or other handicraft? Do you want to share your knowledge and skills whilst practicing your Swedish? Come to Bibblerian Hässelbygård fridays between 10:00-12:00 (break during summer). ', 'Embroider & handicraft while practicing Swedish', '<br>', '', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:17:48'),
(17, 0, 'Fackligt center för papperslösa', 'logo_1435397838741.gif', '', '<div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div>Are you discriminated or harassed at work? <br>Do you work for 20 kronor per hour?<br>Do you get your pay on time?<br>Do you work without brakes?<br><br>These are examples of issues that the people deal with at the Trade Union Center for Undocumented Workers. Today, the center estimates the number of undocumented people in Sweden to be between 30 000 and 50 000 people. They are all in a very vulnerable position and it is not uncommon that that they don''t get paid at all, even though their salary is way below the sum agreed in the collective agreement. <br><br>Are you being discriminated by your employer you are welcome to contact the center and they will try to help you. You can of course be anonymous and the services are free of charge.&nbsp;<div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;">You find them in Stockholm city, close to Odenplan subway station. At Runö Folkhögskola adress Hälsobrunnsgatan 10, or on the freephone service on 020 160 1006.<br></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><a href="http://www.fcfp.se">http://www.fcfp.se</a></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text is written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Undocumented migrants'' rights on the labour market.', 'Fackligt center för papperslösa (The Trade Union Centre for Undocumented Migrants) helps undocumented migrants and asylum-seekers&nbsp;to protect their rights on the labour market.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.fcfp.se', 'info@fcfp.se', 'en', 37, 1, '2015-09-29 17:54:10'),
(20, 0, 'Ingen Människa är Illegal', 'logo_1435317628944.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/Ingen-Människa-är-Illegal-Stockholm-124647770935985/timeline/', '<div style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></div><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">Ingen Människa är Illegal</span><br><div>The No One is Illegal Network (Ingen Människa är Illegal) provides practical support to people who are forced to live undocumented and hidden after having had their applications for asylum rejected. They demand permanent rights of residence for all people who have arrived in Sweden and wish to remain. They believe in a world without borders, a world where no one is illegal. <br><br>The network No One is Illegal works practically and politically with refugees’ and migrants’ rights. <br><br><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">Activities<br></span>Their practical work is to support people who choose to live underground/hidden after having been rejected their application for asylum. This support may be to accompany someone to the doctor, to arrange a place in school for children, to write a new application for asylum, or just to be there as a supporting person when needed. Their work also consists of getting leftover food to give to the migrants, to assist with legal help and to organise solidarity parties to get money for food and rent. <br><br>The network also works politically to raise the issue of asylum seekers and undocumented migrants’ rights. Read more on their website (<a href="http://www.ingenillegal.org/no-one-illegal-world-without-borders" style="font-style: normal;">click here</a>).<br><br><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">About</span><br>The No One is Illegal network organises autonomously and strive within the network to stay away from hierarchy. It consists of local groups in Östersund, Norrbotten, Uppsala, Stockholm and Gothenburg. The local groups are autonomous and organise themselves as they wish according to their manifesto. Activities of the groups may differ a bit but are all related to working practically and politically for the rights of undocumented migrants.<br><br><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">Contact No One is Illegal<br></span>Don’t send any sensitive details about yourself or someone else and be careful even on the phone. Replace the (at) for @ in the address below: <br><br>Email: Stockholm(at)ingenillgal.org<br>Phone: 0707336107 This number is to the Advisory group, call this if you want to set up a meeting with an advisor and get judicial advice. The meetings occur every second Thursday. <br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'A network that supports undocumented migrants.<br>', 'The No One is Illegal Network provides practical support to people who are forced to live undocumented after having had their applications for asylum rejected.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.ingenillegal.org/imai-stockholm', 'Stockholm@ingenillgal.org', 'en', 36, 1, '2015-10-14 12:29:31'),
(21, 0, 'Svenska med baby', 'logo_1441377004319.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/svenskamedbaby', '<div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Svenska med baby</span></div>Svenska med baby ("Swedish with babies") paves the way for new meetings between infants and their parents from all corners of the world. Together we break down segregation, build new bridges and practice our Swedish – through conversation, baby babble and laughter!<br><br>Participation is free. Just turn up at closest venue! Welcome, all parents and children!<br><br>Contact: mail@svenskamedbaby.se<br><br>Follow "Svenska med baby" on facebook.com/svenskamedbaby<br><br><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: italic;">Text written by Svenska med baby. </span><br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Schedule</span>: <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Mondays</span><br>➢ Familjecentralen Skogås (Skogåstorget 12, below Mariakyrkan), kl. 10–11.30. 7/9-30/11<br>➢ Fisksätra kyrka (Fisksätra torg, floor -1), kl.10.30-12. 7/9-30/11<br>➢ Hovsjö kyrka Södertälje (Gröndalsvägen 1), kl. 10.30-12. 7/9-14/12<br>➢ Kista bibliotek (Kista galleria, next to the stage), kl.12.30–14. 7/9-30/11<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tuesdays</span><br>➢ Flemingsbergs familjecentral (Diagnosvägen 5A), kl. 10.00-11.30. 8/9-1/12<br>➢ Alby bibliotek (Albyvägen 6C), kl. 10.30–12.00. 8/9-1/12<br>➢ Tensta bibliotek (Hagstråket 13), kl. 12.30–14. 8/9-1/12<br>➢ Öppna förskolan Rågsved (Rågsveds skolgränd 8), kl. 13–14.30. 8/9-1/12<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Wednesdays</span><br>➢ Farsta bibliotek (Farstagången 8), kl.12.30–14. 9/9-2/12<br>➢ Sollentuna bibliotek (Aniaraplatsen 2), kl. 10.30–12. 16/9-2/12<br>➢ Södertälje stadsbibliotek (Lunagallerian 4), kl. 10-11.30. 9/9-2/12<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Thursdays</span><br>➢ Hallonbergens förskola (Lötsjövägen 67), kl. 12.30–14. 17/9-3/12 <br><span style="font-style: italic;"></span><br>', '"Swedish with babies" brings families and children of different backgrounds and different areas in the city together', '"Swedish with babies" brings families and children of different backgrounds and different areas in the city together.<div><div><br></div></div>', 'http://www.svenskamedbaby.se', 'mail@svenskamedbaby.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 13:14:13'),
(22, 0, 'Amnesty International', 'logo_1435259066321.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/amnestysthlm?fref=ts', '<div><br></div>Amnesty International works with asylum and migration issues, for example by providing general advice and information to asylum-seekers. Amnesty International also investigates individual asylum cases to determine whether we are able to assist with for example country of origin information that can be used by the applicant in the asylum process. In some special cases we can write an opinion but it is very rare that we are able to do so.&nbsp;<div style="font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;"><br>For us to be able to investigate a case, we need copies of all the documents in the asylum process. We look at the cases in the order that we receive them. It may take time before we are able to investigate a case as there are many that contact us and we have limited resources. <br><br>Amnesty International can: <br><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li>Provide general advice and information to asylum-seekers.</li><li>Investigate individual asylum cases to determine whether we are able to assist with, for example, country of origin information.</li></ul>Amnesty International does not operate as legal counsel. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Information about detention units (Förvar)</span><br>To avoid that a person that does not have permission to stay in Sweden goes into hiding in order to escape expulsion or deportation, the person may under certain conditions be placed in a detention unit. A detention unit is a locked facility in which asylum seekers and other detainees are held. The Swedish Migration Agency is responsible for the units in which detainees are normally held. The Migration Agency has detention units in Flen, Gävle, Kållered, Åstorp and Märsta.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;"><br>The rules of detention are set out in Chapters 10 and 11 of the Aliens Act (2005:716). A detention order is issued by the authority handling the case. The police authority or the Migration Agency’s detention orders can be appealed to a migration court. There is no time limit for appeals against detention orders; they may be appealed at any time. A person who is taken into custody for more than three days is entitled to legal counsel.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br>Amnesty’s detention groups (försvarsgrupper) regularly visit the units in Flen, Gävle, Kållered, Åstorp and Märsta. Their mission is to ensure that the detainees’ rights are respected and to provide humanitarian support. They can also help you to get in contact with those working asylum and migration issues at the secretariat and, in some cases, human rights organisations in your home country.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">In case of repatriation to your home country</span><br>If you must return to your home country, we recommend that you contact organisations there, such as the UNHCR, the Red Cross and the International Organization for Migration. <br><br>To get in touch with those working with asylum and migration issues, you are welcome to call the Amnesty International Secretariat on 08-72 90 200 or email flykting@amnesty.se.&nbsp;<br></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Amnesty International Stockholm. Translated into English by Stan för nyanlända.&nbsp;</span></div>', 'Human rights organisation working with asylum and migration issues.<br><div><br></div>', 'Amnesty International is a non-governmental organisation focused on human rights with over 7 million members and supporters around the world.', 'http://www.amnesty.se', 'flykting@amnesty.se', 'en', 35, 1, '2015-09-29 17:45:01'),
(24, 0, 'Al Kompis', 'logo_1435258116724.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/alkompis.se', 'Al Kompis is a newspaper in Arabic that you can read online, get in printed version or listen to on the radio.&nbsp;<div style="font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;">It is one of Sweden’s largest newspapers in social media and has a Facebook following that is almost as large as the Swedish evening newspaper Aftonbladet.se.&nbsp;<div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div>The online newspaper is in Arabic and reports about a large range of different topics for the Arabic speaking population in Sweden and abroad.<br> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Read it here:<br></span>Alkompis.se<br>Al-tid.se<br>Al-media.se<br>Alkompis.fm (Radio)<br>Alkompismedianetwork.se</div><div><br><a href="https://www.facebook.com/alkompis.se">https://www.facebook.com/alkompis.se</a></div><div><a href="http://alkompis.se">http://alkompis.se</a><br>Contact: info@alkompis.com</div></div></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Swedish news in Arabic.', 'Al Kompis is a Swedish newspaper in Arabic.', 'http://alkompis.se', 'info@alkompis.com', 'en', 15, 1, '2015-09-29 17:13:23'),
(25, 1, 'Det Stora Knytkalaset', 'logo_1435306996508.png', '', 'Det Stora Knytkalaset is a non-profit and politically and religiously independent association working for multiculturalism. We meet, do cultural activities and have fun together. Here, people of different ethnic and cultural backgrounds come together to create new cultural activities and fun and meaningful meeting places.<br><br>Anyone is welcome to the following events.<div><br><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Language café</span><br>Is run in collaboration with Pangea. We meet and practice Swedish, have fun together, learn new things and meet new friends. We invite unaccompanied minors, SFI-students and other newly arrived youth. We are several mentors in this group that can become your link to Sweden.</div><div><br>Location: Knytkalaset, CMR:s space, Hallonbergsplan 5, floor 3, Hallonbergen Center. Free of charge.&nbsp;</div><div>For opening hours: email info@knytkalaset.se</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"> The People’s Café<br></span>“Fika” (have coffee with others), meet interesting people and practice your Swedish. The People’s Café has different themes that its members arrange themselves. There will be culture, sharing stories, health, laughter, music and dance.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Free of charge.&nbsp;</div><div>For opening hours: http://knytkalaset.se/?p=505 <br>Location: Festvåningen (The events facility), cellar level, in Allaaktivtetshuset, Sturegatan 10, Sundbyberg.</div><div><br>Contact: Telefon:  0708-197205<br>E-post: info@knytkalaset.se</div></div>', 'Cultural activities and meeting places in Sundbyberg', 'Det Stora Knytkalaset is an association in Sundbyberg that arranges cultural activities and meeting places for all.&nbsp;', 'http://knytkalaset.se', 'info@knytkalaset.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:23:16'),
(26, 1, 'Homework Assistance', 'logo_1435308368773.png', '', 'We offer homework assistance for unaccompanied minors in Rågsved. <br><br>For IM (Individuell Människohjälp) is the homework assistance more than just a help with the homework; its about creating a meeting between people who otherwise wouldn’t meet.<br><br>Mondays and Wednesdays 18.00-20.00 in Rågsved<br>', 'Homework Assistance Rågsved<br>', '', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-ragsved', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:46:08'),
(27, 1, 'Language Café', 'logo_1435308745598.png', '', 'The language café is open for anybody who wants to get a basic understanding of the Swedish language and at the same time meet new friends and share experiences and thoughts. <br><br>Particularly welcome are the people who stand outside the social and educational system, such as asylum seekers.<br><br>During the classes we practice grammar, socialize, read easy books and have conversations.<br><br>The language café is every Sunday 13.00-16.00. It’s a part of the Silent University; an autonomous platform for asylum seekers, refugees and undocumented migrants.<br><br>For registration and info, please contact  fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se<br><br>http://abfstockholm.se/event/2014/11/the-silent-university-sprakcafe-7/', 'Autonomous platform for asylum seekers, refugees and undocumented migrants', '', 'http://abfstockholm.se/event/2014/11/the-silent-university-sprakcafe-7/', 'fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-06-26 11:52:25'),
(28, 0, 'Fristadsfonden', 'logo_1435310471351.jpg', '', '<div><br></div>Fristadsfonden helps asylum-seeking refugees who are threatened by deportation and cannot return to their home countries. Many have been victims of persecution and torture or have traumatic war experiences. The asylum-seekers supported by the fund have well-founded fear of returning to the countries they have fled from and are therefore forced to hide in our country.<div style="font-style: normal;"><br>The fund contributes financially for you to obtain a legal counsel after we have done a careful examination of your case and found it necessary to submit a new application for asylum that can alter the previous wrong decision.</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br>In order to convince the authorities that the refugees have grounds for asylum, they have funded numerous torture investigations, medical reports and psychologist certificates. They also pay for interpretation costs in contacts with the authorities, for example in the case of an investigation of torture injuries.</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br>Fristadsfonden was founded by Vänsterpartiet (the Left Party) in 1995. The fund has helped many refugees obtain permanent residence permits. It is entirely non-profit.<br>If you want to get in touch with the board, email anita.dorazio[at]gmail.com.<br></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'For asylum-seeking refugees who are threatened by deportation.&nbsp;', 'Fristadsfonden helps asylum-seeking refugees threatened by deportation and who cannot return to their home countries file a new application for asylum.<div><br></div>', 'http://fristadsfonden.se', '', 'en', 34, 1, '2015-09-29 17:44:17'),
(29, 0, 'Kompis Sverige', 'logo_1441367217864.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/Kompissverige?fref=ts', '<div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Kompis Sverige</span></div>Kompis Sverige matches newcomers with established Swedes to create new friendships in a society where it can be difficult to get to know one another in an equal and natural way.<br><br>They conduct interviews with new and established Swedes. They look at interests, life situation and personality. They always match women with women and men with men. They also match families with children.<div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">You and your new friend meet for the first time in Kompis Sveriges facilities and find out more about each other. After that the match is finished and you are now ”kompisar”! The remaining time it is up to you and your friend to decide what you want to do. Their only requirement is that you will see each other for at least six months, but their hope is of course to create lasting friendships.<div><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Requirements: <br></span>-	You have to be over 18 years of age. <br>-	You have a residence permit in Sweden (you may have lived here for a short or long period of time but you feel that it is difficult to make established friends).<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">For registration:&nbsp;</span></div><div>Email your name and a brief descrption of why you want to become a ”kompis” (friend) to <span style="text-decoration: underline;">info@kompissverige.se</span>. They will then contact you to schedule a time for the interview where you get to know more about Kompis Sverige. It takes around 30 minutes and they ask you questions in order to find the best possible friend for you. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Times of interview:<br></span>Tuesdays between 18.00-21.00 in the meeting place Kupan, Östgötagatan 67, Stockholm. You need to book an appointment.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Why Kompis Sverige?<br></span>New Swedes often want to have a Swedish friend to faster understand Swedish society, speak Swedish with and learn more about Swedish culture. Established often want to know more about what it''s like to be new in Sweden, get to know a new culture and get the opportunity to exchange experiences and socialize with a person from a different background.<br><br>By creating friendships on an individual level given the conditions necessary for a properly functioning multicultural society - a Sweden where the boundaries between established and new Swedes erased. Read more at:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.kompissverige.se/" style="font-weight: normal;">http://www.kompissverige.se/</a>.</div></div><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Text is written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Creates friendships between new and established Swedes.<br>', 'Kompis Sverige is a project that arranges meetings between new and nestablished Swedes. If you have recently moved to Sweden they will help nyou get to know a&nbsp; person who since long is established in Sweden!<div><br></div>', 'http://www.kompissverige.se/', 'info@kompissverige.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-11-21 16:56:20'),
(30, 0, 'Internationella Bekantskaper Stockholm', 'logo_1435320099217.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/internationellabekantskaper?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Internationella Bekantskaper</span></div>Internationella Bekantskaper is an independent and non-profit organisation that brings people together - those who speak Swedish and those who want to learn Swedish in order to get establish in Swedish society. <br><br>Knowledge of the language is important in Swedish society. To be able to speak Swedish makes it easier to participate in society and find a job. Knowledge of language makes it easier for individuals and groups to form friendship despite different mother tongues. <br><br>Internationella Bekantskaper envisages a Sweden where all feel at home using Swedish, and feel able to participate in society. <br><br>The organisation uses conversation and language training to create opportunities for people of differing cultural background to meet. Its activities take place mainly at schools or in areas where many newcomers to the country live.<br><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Read more about their activities and how to participate:&nbsp;</span><div><ul><li>Homework assistance in Rinkeby</li><li>Homework assistance in Tensta</li><li>Svenska med baby ("Swedish with Babies") <br></li></ul></div><div><br>For further information about their work as medpratare(conversation supporters) in SFI classes – adult education/Swedish for Immigrants – and språkstödjare(language supporters) for secondary school pupils, please see our website. <br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Contact:&nbsp;</span></div></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><a href="http://bekantskaper.se/">http://bekantskaper.se/</a></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><div>pelle.friman@bekantskaper.se</div></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">070 269 20 53</div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Internationella-Bekantskaper/183701975062013?sk=timeline">Facebook Internationella Bekantskaper</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Internationella Bekantskaper.</span><br></div>', 'Language exchange between new and established Swedes!', 'Internationella Bekantskaper ("International Acquaintances") is an independent and non-profit organisation that brings people together - those who speak Swedish and those who want to learn Swedish in order to get establish in Swedish society.&nbsp;<div><br></div>', 'http://bekantskaper.se/', 'pelle.friman@bekantskaper.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 11:53:48'),
(31, 0, 'IFFI Stockholm', 'logo_1435399083973.jpg', '', 'IFFI Stockholm (International Association for Immigrant Women) is a local branch of the national RIFFI (Swedish Federation of Immigrant Women’s Organisations). It is open for all immigrant women irrespective of their nationality and their political and religious background. It is politically and religiously neutral and it offers a meeting place for women from all over the world. <br><br>IFFI Stockholm has around 700 members and it offers among other things: <br><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li>Courses in Swedish, English, Spanish, sewing, art, swimming</li><li>Various support groups for women with psychosocial, social or judicial problems</li><li>Activities such as Open House for highlighting and discussing current issues, information on legal rights and responsibilities in the Swedish society, consumer guidance, cultural programmes</li><li>Several projects to empower women and support women and their families with the integration process</li></ul><br>Join them by becoming a member!<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">For more information: <br></span><a href="http://www.iffi-stockholm.se/page10.html">http://www.iffi-stockholm.se/page10.html</a><br><a href="http://www.iffi-stockholm.se">http://www.iffi-stockholm.se</a><br>info@iffi-stockholm.se<br>08-342199 during office hours 9.00-16.00<br><div><br></div><div>To read about RIFFI:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.riffi.nu">http://www.riffi.nu</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'International Association for Immigrant Women.', 'For immigrant women of all nationalities in the Stockholm area.', 'http://www.iffi-stockholm.se', 'info@iffi-stockholm.se', 'en', 33, 1, '2015-09-29 16:59:46'),
(32, 0, 'Sveriges Ensamkommandes Förening', 'logo_1435398449128.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/pages/SEF-Sveriges-Ensamkommandes-F%C3%B6rening/368931846455727', '<div style="font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Sveriges Ensamkommandes Förening (SEF - The Swedish Association for Unaccompanied Minors)</span><br>The association works to protect and encourage unaccompanied minors’ cultural and social interests. It is active all over Sweden. It organises activities, offers mentoring for unaccompanied children and young people, monitors issues related to unaccompanied minors and gives lectures to other organisations and the authorities.<br><br>It supports its members to find their place in society by:<br></span><ul><li><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;">Spreading knowledge and information about Swedish society and the many Swedish associations</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;">Organising activities (sport, art, science, pedagogy, culture and social activities and so on)</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;">Networking with other associations with a similar agenda</span></li><li><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;">Organising meetings with organsiations/individuals and the members of SEF to link knowledge, experience and public interests.</span></li></ul><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: small;">The associations exists through the contribution of its members.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Who can become a member? <br></span>Anyone who was unaccompanied when arriving in Sweden or any other western country is welcome to become a member. Other people who want to support our organisation are welcome to become supportive members (stödmedlemmar). Visit our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/SEF-Sveriges-Ensamkommandes-F%C3%B6rening/368931846455727">Facebook page</a>.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">About SEF<br></span>SEF belongs to the national association SEF Riksförbund. SEF Riksförbund was formed on December 14 in 2013 as the first ever national association by and for unaccompanied minors. <br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända. </span><br></span></div>', 'The Swedish Association for Unaccompanied Minors<br>', '<div>They help and support unaccompanied minors in Stockholm to find their place in the new society.<br><br><br></div>', 'https://www.facebook.com/pages/SEF-Sveriges-Ensamkommandes-F%C3%B6rening/368931846455727', '', 'en', 32, 1, '2015-09-29 17:04:05'),
(33, 0, 'Stockholms Asylbyrå', 'logo_1435400117559.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/Stockholms-Asylbyrå-AB-173117172736006/timeline/', 'The lawyers at Stockholm Asylbyrå (Asylum Bureau) have specialist competence within asylum and migration law. They help individuals who apply for asylum, residence permit      and work permit in Sweden. <br><br>They also assist individuals regarding swedish citizenship, custody and crimes of an international nature.<br> <br><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">They offer free telephone consultation!</span><br>+46-8-5000 75 39<br><br><a href="http://asylbyran.se/?lang=en" style="font-style: normal;">http://asylbyran.se/</a><br><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Specialist in asylum and migration law.<br>', 'Free telephone consultation for questions concerning asylum and migration law.<br>', 'http://asylbyran.se/?lang=en', '', 'en', 31, 1, '2015-09-29 17:04:28'),
(34, 0, 'National Association of Afro Swedes (ASR) Stockholm', 'logo_1435437373180.jpg', '', '<div><br></div>Afrosvenskarnas riksförbund (National Association of Afro Swedes - ASR) works to improve daily life for all Afro-Swedes in Sweden through activities, projects and information. ASR is a humanitarian, cultural and non-profit organisation. It is politically and religiously neutral and has five regional branches in Malmö, Göteborg, Stockholm, Jönköping and Umeå. <br><br>ASR in Stockholm is open to Afro-Swedes born in Stockholm county. It organises activities within the frameworks of culture, education, antiracism, social issues and preservation of African culture. <br><br>You can take part in the activities and become involved with the work by becoming a member. Contact them by phone +46(8)6438185,+46(8)6439036 or by sending a message on their website: <a href="http://www.afrosvenskarna.se/index.php?option=com_contact&amp;view=contact&amp;id=3%3Aasr-stockholm&amp;catid=36%3Acontacts&amp;Itemid=54">http://www.afrosvenskarna.se/</a>.<br><br>You are also welcome to visit Café Pan Afrika, located in Stockholm, which is a forum where Africa is discussed from an African perspective. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/cafepanafrika/timeline">https://www.facebook.com/cafepanafrika/timeline&nbsp;</a><br>', 'National Association of Afro-Swedes in Stockholm', 'Local association in Stockholm belonging to the National Association of Afro-Swedes', 'http://www.afrosvenskarna.se', '', 'en', 30, 1, '2015-09-29 16:50:10'),
(35, 0, 'RFSL Stockholm', 'logo_1435440908514.jpg', '', 'RFSL is an association that works for homosexual, bisexual, transgender and queer people, their relatives and friends. To read about their work in Stockholm, visit their website:&nbsp;<a href="http://rfslstockholm.se/om-oss/language/english/">http://rfslstockholm.se/</a><div><br><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Immigration consultant</span><br>Are you in Sweden on vacation? Have you sought asylum in Sweden because of your sexual orientation? Have you come to Sweden to join a family member?<br><br>RFSL Stockholm offers you advice and assistance in your juridical needs of the first instance in Stockholm, Sweden.<br><br>They also assist you in contacting: the Migration Board (Migrationsverket), SFI (Swedish for foreigners), health centers, Social Insurance Office (Försäkringkassan), National Tax Board (Skatteverket), Public Employment Services (arbetsförmedlingen), the Police (Polis) etc.<br><br>The counsellor for foreigners attends to HIV positive individuals and their families, assists you in contacting Venhälsan clinic and Sesam City clinic, the Posithiv group, Noah’s Ark and other organizations (ONG) in Sweden that work with HIV positive individuals and are engaged in preventive activities against HIV/AIDS and STI (sexually transmitted infections).<br><br>Prices:<br>Appointments are charged according to the following prices:<br>* Employed persons: 100 kr per visit.<br>* Unemployed, students, pensioners, persons requesting asylum (without a job), undocumented migrants, HIV positive individuals and persons who request HIV/AIDS support: 0 kr<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Contact:<br></span>Phone: 08-501 629 56<br>Email: pablo@rfslstockholm.se<br>Phone hours:<br>Mondays, Wednesdays and Thursdays: 10:00-12:00<br><br>Welcome!<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">About RFSL: <br></span>RFSL works for homosexual, bisexual, transgender and queer people, their relatives and friends. Their purpose is to promote a society distinguished by respect for the equal rights and opportunities of all people – irrespective of gender, sexual identity, gender identity or gender expression, HIV status, ethnic affiliation, religion or other belief, functional capacity, age or socioeconomic background. RFSL is a non-profit organisation. It is non-partisan and not affiliated with any religious organisation. <a href="http://www.rfsl.se/?p=3298">http://www.rfsl.se/?p=3298</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div></div>', 'The Swedish Federation for Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender Rights', '<div>RFSL is the Swedish Federation for Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender Rights. RFSL Stockholm is one of its local branches.&nbsp;</div>', 'http://www.rfsl.se', '', 'en', 28, 1, '2015-09-29 16:47:36');
