(8, 1, 'Language fika', 'logo_1441366283378.jpg', '', 'Do you like to meet new people? Would you like to practice your Swedish? Anybody is invited to the Språkfika to sit down, have a coffee and speak Swedish for an hour or two. <br><br>When? 17:00-19:00 every second week (see dates in calendar) <br>Where? IM-office, Västgötagränd 17. OBS! Entrance from Fatbursparken<br><br><br>DATES<br><br>tuesday 1 september<br>thursday 17 september<br>tuesday 29 september<br>thursday 15 oktober<br>tuesday 27 oktober<br>thursday 12 november<br>tuesday 24 november<br>thursday 10 december<br><br>Website:  http://www.manniskohjalp.se/node/2017<br>Contact: jonathan.osterlund@manniskohjalp.se <br>', 'Have coffee and practice your Swedish<br>', 'Join us for a coffee, meet new people and speak Swedish! .<br>', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/node/2017', '', 'en', 10, 1, '2015-10-06 14:57:20'),
(9, 1, 'Homework Assistance Tensta', 'logo_1444122301994.png', '', 'The homework assistance is a place for children and youth that have another first language than Swedish. For IM homework assistance is more than just help with the homework. Its about offering a space where people, who usually don’t meet, can meet. <br><br>Mondays 17.00 - 18.45 at Tensta bibliotek<br>Wednesdays 16.30 - 18.30 at Tensta konsthall<br>', 'Homework Assistance: Tensta', '<br>', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-tensta', '', 'en', 12, 1, '2015-10-06 12:05:01'),
(10, 1, 'Homework Assistance: Hässelby', 'logo_1445861169273.png', '', 'Hässelby:  Mondays and tuesdays 17.00-18.45 at Hässelby gårds lärandecenter.<br><br>IMs homework assistance in Hässelby is a space for children from two schools in Hässelby Gård, where more than 40 languages are spoken. Many or the children recently came to sweden, has another mothertongue than Swedish and few have the possibility to get help with homework at home.<br><br><a href="http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-hasselby">Website</a><br>', 'Homework Assistance: Hässelby', '<br>', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-hasselby', '', 'en', 9, 1, '2015-10-26 14:06:09'),
(11, 1, 'Homework assistance ', 'logo_1441365830690.png', '', 'Kista Bibliotek with the Red Cross and Mattecentrum<br><br>Do you need assistance with your homework? Go and get help from volunteers from the Red Cross and Mattecentrum.<br><br>Every Thursday between 17.00 and 19.00 their talented homework helpers are stationed in the library.<br><br>It is a free service and you don’t have to sign up before- Welcome!<br><br><a href="https://biblioteket.stockholm.se/kalender/l%C3%A4xhj%C3%A4lp-p%C3%A5-kista-bibliotek-med-r%C3%B6da-korset-och-mattecentrum">Website </a><br><br>On Mondays Kista Galaxy offers homework assistance in the library 17.00-19.00 i', 'Homework Assistance Kista Bibliotek<br>', 'Do you need help with your homework? Please join us on thursdays or mondays! <br>', 'https://biblioteket.stockholm.se/kalender/l%C3%A4xhj%C3%A4lp-p%C3%A5-kista-bibliotek-med-r%C3%B6da-korset-och-mattecentrum', '', 'en', 3, 1, '2015-09-23 11:17:11'),
(12, 1, 'Handicraft and Swedish ', 'logo_1435306668176.jpg', '', 'Do you like to embroider, knit or other handicraft? Do you want to share your knowledge and skills whilst practicing your Swedish? Come to Bibblerian Hässelbygård fridays between 10:00-12:00 (break during summer). ', 'Embroider & handicraft while practicing Swedish', '<br>', '', '', 'en', 2, 0, '2015-06-26 11:17:48'),
(13, 1, 'Det Stora Knytkalaset', 'logo_1441365486246.png', '', 'Det Stora Knytkalaset is a non-profit and politically and religiously independent association working for multiculturalism. They meet, do cultural activities and have fun together. There, people of different ethnic and cultural backgrounds come together to create new cultural activities and fun and meaningful meeting places.<br><br>Everyone is welcome to the following events.<div><br><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Language café</span><br>Is run in collaboration with Pangea. They meet and practice Swedish, have fun together, learn new things and meet new friends. They invite unaccompanied minors, SFI-students and other newly arrived youth. They have several mentors in this group that can become your link to Sweden.</div><div><br>Location: Knytkalaset, CMR:s space, Hallonbergsplan 5, floor 3, Hallonbergen Center. Free of charge.&nbsp;</div><div>For opening hours: email info@knytkalaset.se</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"> The People’s Café<br></span>“Fika” (have coffee with others), meet interesting people and practice your Swedish. The People’s Café has different themes that its members arrange themselves. There will be culture, sharing stories, health, laughter, music and dance.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Free of charge.&nbsp;</div><div>For opening hours: http://knytkalaset.se/?p=505 <br>Location: Festvåningen (The events facility), cellar level, in Allaaktivtetshuset, Sturegatan 10, Sundbyberg.</div><div><br>Contact: Telefon:  0708-197205<br>E-post: info@knytkalaset.se</div></div>', 'Cultural activities and meeting places in Sundbyberg', 'Det Stora Knytkalaset is an association in Sundbyberg that arranges cultural activities and meeting places for all. ', 'http://knytkalaset.se', 'info@knytkalaset.se', 'en', 7, 1, '2015-09-04 14:18:06'),
(14, 1, 'Homework Assistance Rågsved', 'logo_1445861195222.png', '', 'They offer homework assistance for unaccompanied minors in Rågsved. <br><br>For IM (Individuell Människohjälp) is the homework assistance more than just a help with the homework; its about creating a meeting between people who otherwise wouldn’t meet.<br><br>Mondays and Wednesdays 18.00-20.00 in Rågsved<br>', 'Homework Assistance Rågsved<br>', '', 'http://www.manniskohjalp.se/projekt/laxhjalp-ragsved', '', 'en', 1, 1, '2015-10-26 14:06:35'),
(15, 1, 'Language Café', 'logo_1435308745598.png', '', 'The language café is open for anybody who wants to get a basic understanding of the Swedish language and at the same time meet new friends and share experiences and thoughts. <br><br>Particularly welcome are the people who stand outside the social and educational system, such as asylum seekers.<br><br>During the classes we practice grammar, socialize, read easy books and have conversations.<br><br>The language café is every Sunday 13.00-16.00. It’s a part of the Silent University; an autonomous platform for asylum seekers, refugees and undocumented migrants.<br><br>For registration and info, please contact  fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se<br><br>http://abfstockholm.se/event/2014/11/the-silent-university-sprakcafe-7/', 'Autonomous platform for asylum seekers, refugees and undocumented migrants', '-', 'http://abfstockholm.se/event/2014/11/the-silent-university-sprakcafe-7/', 'fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se', 'en', 4, 1, '2015-10-06 14:56:37'),
(16, 1, 'Tensta Art Gallery: Citizen to citizen', 'logo_1435756279796.jpg', '', 'Medborgare till medborgare aims to create a meeting place for newcomers who need support, advice and knowledge about the Swedish society. It is an advice service where you can ask anything between how to contact authorities, where to practice your Swedish and how to meet like-minded.<br><br>Because the group meets in the art gallery in Tensta, it also discusses society in reference to current art exhibitions and issues in society.<br><br>The group meets Tuesdays 12.00-14..00. For registration and info, please contact  fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se<div><br><a href="http://abfstockholm.se/event/2015/04/medborgare-till-medborgare-11-12/">http://abfstockholm.se/event/2015/04/medborgare-till-medborgare-11-12/</a><br><a href="http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/">http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/</a><br></div>', 'A meeting place for newcomers in Sweden', 'Medborgare till medborgare (Citizen to citizen) is arranged by Tensta Art Gallery in Stockholm. It is a meeting place for newcomers in Sweden.', 'http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/', 'fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se', 'en', 14, 1, '2015-07-01 16:11:19'),
(39, 1, 'Fånga framtiden tillsammans', 'logo_1441369827441.png', '', '<span style="font-weight: bold;">Fånga framtiden tillsammans<br><br></span>Fånga framtiden tillsammans is a non-profit organisation that supports the integration of young adults and unaccompanied minors. <br><br>They meet on Gotlandsgatan every Wednesday between 18:00-20:00. Young adults up to 25 years old can come and get homework assistance, find motivation for further studies, attend interesting lectures and get help to become a drivers license. <br><br>They also support youth who are about to be reunited with their families and help to become independent and prepare for the future.<br><br>The goal of Fånga framtiden tillsammans is to prevent social exclusion and to get young adults to feel like a part of the Swedish society. They focus on individual support and aim to continuously develop new ways of including young adults in the Swedish society. <br><br>Visit their <a href="https://www.facebook.com/fangaframtidentillsammans">Facebook page</a><br>Or  email them at framtidentillsammans@gmail.com for further questions. <br><br>Adress <br> Gotlandsgatan 70,<br>116 65 Stockholm <br><br>', 'Advice and support for unaccompanied minors', 'Advice and support for unaccompanied minors', 'https://www.facebook.com/fangaframtidentillsammans', 'framtidentillsammans@gmail.com', 'en', 8, 1, '2015-09-22 16:15:08'),
(40, 1, 'Meeting place for women - Akalla', 'logo_1441391257520.jpg', '', 'The Salvation Army’s centre in Akalla offers an all-female meeting place for women with foreign background. The centre is open:<br><br>Monday 9:30 – 15:00 <br>Tuesday 9:30 – 15:00 <br>Wednesday 9:30 – 12:00 and 15:30-19:00<br>Thursday 9:30 – 15:00 <br><br>Activities offered at the centre are: <br>Swedish training<br>Social activities<br>Activities for children<br>Baking<br>Sewing, etc. <br><br>Visit their <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Fr%C3%A4lsningsarm%C3%A9n-Akalla/253878894792342?fref=ts">Facebook page</a> for more information and to get in contact! <br>', 'The Salvation Army’s only-for-women meeting place in Akalla', 'The Salvation Army’s only-for-women meeting place in Akalla', '', '', 'en', 13, 1, '2015-09-04 21:27:37'),
(41, 1, 'Legal Advice at Kista Library', 'logo_1441800784371.png', '', 'Kista Library gives you the opportunity of meeting a lawyer for 15 minutes of personal legal advice. <br><br>', 'Ledal advice in Arabic, Kurdish, Farsi and Swedish<br>', '-<br>', '', '', 'en', 5, 1, '2015-10-06 14:48:57'),
(51, 1, 'Fisksatra.se', 'logo_1444224026533.png', '', 'Fisksatra.se is a gathering point for things in Fisksätra..<br>', '<div style="font-style: normal;">A calender of activities happening in Fisksätra!</div>', 'Find out what is happening in Fisksätra! A website created by volunteers.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.fisksatra.se', '', 'en', 15, 1, '2015-10-20 11:23:58'),
(52, 1, 'Meet My City', 'logo_1444229359287.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/Meetmycitynow/timeline', '<div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><span style="font-style: italic;"><br></span></div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Meet My City</span><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">&nbsp;is a new integration project found in Stockholm, Vienna, Gdansk, Vilnius, Perm, Moscow, Sankt Petersburg and Berlin. <br><br>The project is for you who have recently migrated to Sweden. It matches you with a person who lives in your city and who can give you a personalized guided tour of his or her favourite part of town. After you sign up, you get an email with suggestions of dates, locations and what to do!<br><br>The idea is simple. People from different backgrounds meet. They show each other the hometown where they live. It is a personalised guided tour.<br><br>The project aims to create a platform to build bridges between migrants and local communities. <br><br>The people behind the project believe that a person who has migrated becomes a local when bonds are tied to the people and the city where he or she lives. If you have your own sweet spots in the area where you live, a network of friends and perhaps an involvement in local events – you are a part of the society.  <br><br>Visit their website to read more and sign up!<br><a href="http://www.meetmycity.org">www.meetmycity.org</a><br></span>', 'Personalized guided tours by locals for newcomers in Stockholm.<div><br></div>', 'The idea behind Meet My City is simple. People from different backgrounds meet. They show each other the hometown where they live. It is a personalised guided tour.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.meetmycity.org', '', 'en', 11, 0, '2015-10-08 06:15:05'),
(53, 1, 'Tjejhuset Södertälje', 'logo_1445432489677.png', 'https://sv-se.facebook.com/tjejhuset.sodertalje/', '<div style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tjejhuset</span></div><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div>Tjejhuset is an open activity for all girls between 13-23 years. For us, you can come as you are creating, talking, doing your homework or just being. We eat a meal together every day at 16:30. There are plenty snacks and everything is free. To have your own place to come to create peace.<br><br>We are three adults is in place and we always have time for you. Welcome to us. An oasis just for girls.<br><br>Opening hours:<br>Tuesdays 2:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.<br>Wednesdays 2:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.<br>Thursdays 2:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.<br><br>Phone: 08-550 15:01 Mobile: 070-751 08 01<br><br><span style="font-weight: normal; font-style: italic;">Text written by Tjejhuset Södertälje.</span>', 'Open activities in Södertälje for girls between 13-23 years. Three afternoons / evenings a week.', 'Tjejhuset offers open activities for girls between 13-23 years. Three afternoons / evenings a week. In Södertälje and soon in Bandhagen.<div><br></div>', 'http://tjejhuset.se/', 'johanna@tjejhuset.se', 'en', 6, 1, '2015-10-21 16:02:04');
