(36, 0, 'The Sisters'' Shelter Somaya', 'logo_1435443621601.png', '', '<span style="font-weight: bold;">The Sisters’ Shelter Somaya<br></span>Are you female and a victim of violence? You might be beaten, threatened, harassed, or called derogatory things? Want advice? Want support?<br> <br>Want to talk to someone who really understands you without judging you? Do you want to be able to talk to someone without telling them who you are?<br> <br>The Sisters'' Shelter Somaya is a non-profit organisation that operates shelters for both women and girls. They are the first and only shelter that has more than ten years of experience and knowledge of how it is to be a victim of violence and to have a different background than Swedish.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">You can call them</span> if you, or someone you know, become a victim of physical, sexual, economical and mental violence. They listen, they believe in you, and they offer you advice, support and help to move forward.<br> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Somaya can inform you</span> of your rights and opportunities, and also provide you with suggestions on other good advisers, good lawyers, or assist you in any other possible way.<br> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Somaya also offer interpretations, translations and other practical things</span> in contact with police, lawyers, health care and governments. They support you in your own choices and guide you toward "self-help".<br> <br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Somaya can also provide sheltered accommodations.</span> They have sworn secrecy and everything you say remains with us. You can remain anonymous if you wish.<br><br>Languages spoken: amarinja, arabiska, deutsch, english, español, farsi, francais, grekiska, kurdiska, tigrinja, turkce.&nbsp;<div><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Dial 020 - 81 82 83</span><br>The number is free and will not appear on the phone bill.<br> <br>E-mail kvinnojouren@somaya.se<br><a href="http://www.somaya.se/start/ditt-språk-5936637">http://www.somaya.se/</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'Helpline and shelter for women.', 'The Sisters'' Shelter Somaya is a non-profit organisation which operates shelters for both women and girls. They offer a helpline in several different languages.', 'http://www.somaya.se', 'kvinnojouren@somaya.se', 'en', 27, 1, '2015-09-29 16:45:38'),
(37, 0, 'MANUEL', 'logo_1435445282483.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/manuelkontaktnat/timeline', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">MANUEL</span></div>MANUEL is a contact, friend and support network for immigrants (adults and seniors) in the Stockholm area. It has been around since 2000.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>The purpose of the service is to offer help and support in a person’s own language when he/she suffers from, for example, a disease, family tragedy, judicial problems or other hardships. Language barriers and cultural difference can make those situations even more difficult.&nbsp;<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br>Do you, a family member, a friend or an acquaintance need help? Don’t hesitate to contact MANUEL! <br><br>Address: Södergården on Götgatan 37, 116 21 Stockholm (go to T-Medborgarplatsen, walk towards Slussen. Södergården is in the first block on the right side). <br><br>They are open Monday-Thursday from 12-16.00. <br><br>Contact: <br>Kontakt-manuel@telia.com<br>070 643 69 66<br><a href="http://www.kontaktmanuel.se">http://www.kontaktmanuel.se</a><br><a href="https://www.facebook.com/manuelkontaktnat">https://www.facebook.com/manuelkontaktnat </a><br><br>The service is financed mainly by Socialnämnden in Stockholm and Landstingets Hälso- och sjukvårdsnämnd. <br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">The text is written by Stan för nyanlända. </span><br></div></div>', 'Network and support service for adults and seniors.', 'Manuel is a network and support service for adult and senior immigrants in the Stockholm area.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.kontaktmanuel.se', 'Kontakt-manuel@telia.com', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 12:31:13'),
(38, 1, 'Tensta Art Gallery: Citizen to citizen', 'logo_1435756279796.jpg', '', 'Medborgare till medborgare aims to create a meeting place for newcomers who need support, advice and knowledge about the Swedish society. It is an advice service where you can ask anything between how to contact authorities, where to practice your Swedish and how to meet like-minded.<br><br>Because the group meets in the art gallery in Tensta, it also discusses society in reference to current art exhibitions and issues in society.<br><br>The group meets Tuesdays 12.00-14..00. For registration and info, please contact  fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se<div><br><a href="http://abfstockholm.se/event/2015/04/medborgare-till-medborgare-11-12/">http://abfstockholm.se/event/2015/04/medborgare-till-medborgare-11-12/</a><br><a href="http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/">http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/</a><br></div>', 'A meeting place for newcomers in Sweden', 'Medborgare till medborgare (Citizen to citizen) is arranged by Tensta Art Gallery in Stockholm. It is a meeting place for newcomers in Sweden.', 'http://www.tenstakonsthall.se/', 'fahyma@tenstakonsthall.se', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-07-01 16:11:19'),
(39, 0, 'The Liberal Fund for Refugees', 'logo_1435474859722.png', '', '<div><br></div>Liberala flyktingfonden (the Liberal Fund for Refugees) is a charitable fund run by The Liberal Youth of Sweden (LUF). It supports hidden refugees in Sweden with money and legal advice.<br><br>You can apply for money from the fund if you are a hidden refugee (your asylum application has been rejected by the Migration Board and you face deportation), and you feel that your reasons for asylum have not been properly considered and you want the chance to apply again or simply survive in Sweden.<div><br><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li>What they do: Receive applications from hidden refugees.</li><li>What they review in your application: Are you a refugee? Then you get money!</li><li>What they do to help: Give advice, provide contact and money for a lawyer, food, medicine and rent.&nbsp;</li><li>What they wish for: that they didn’t need to exist.&nbsp;</li></ul>You can read more about the application requirements on their application page: <a href="http://www.luf.se/om-oss/flyktingfonden/150-2/">http://www.luf.se/om-oss/flyktingfonden/150-2/</a><br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Contact</span><br>For general questions about the fund and what is needed to apply, contact flyktingfonden@luf.se<br><br>Phone number: 08-55922743.<div>Leave a message with your name and phone number and they will call you back.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">About the fund: <br></span>The fund is sponsored by gifts from the public. It is run voluntarily by a number of committed youths and all the money is distributed to people in need without any administrative charges. <br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända</span><br></div></div>', 'Charitable fund that supports hidden refugees in Sweden', 'The Liberal Fund for Refugees is a charitable fund run by The Liberal Youth of Sweden (LUF). It supports hidden refugees in Sweden with money and legal advice.', 'http://www.luf.se/om-oss/flyktingfonden/150-2/', 'flyktingfonden@luf.se', 'en', 26, 1, '2015-09-29 16:42:55'),
(40, 0, 'Caritas Sweden', 'logo_1444821999512.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/IAmCaritas?fref=ts', '<div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Caritas Sweden</span></div><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Caritas gives support and advice to asylum seekers, refugees and undocumented migrants. In the last years they have also supported people who have chosen to return to their home countries. They work with lobbying work nationally and in the European Union concerning refugee- and trafficking issues.</span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Caritas want to offer people in vulnerable situations a safe place where you can get advice, counselling, information about the Swedish society and human support. You are welcome to visit them during the day time to ask questions and get help from their central organisation. They can also put you in contact with any of their catholic congregations in Sweden. </span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Caritas offers individuals support and continuously meet people who are in need of help for individual counselling. Once the needs are identified, they assist with the concrete support and the counselling we are capable to. </span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><b>Caritas Sweden has a toll-free number for&nbsp;counseling.&nbsp;</b></span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;"><b>020 – 462 664</b></span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Monday to Friday 09:00 to 14:00 (when closed you can leave a message – they listen through the messages on a general basis). Everyone is welcome to use this number to get help with questions regarding refugees, asylum seekers, undocumented migrants and trafficking victims. </span></font><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Caritas Sweden is a Catholic charitable association founded in 1946 to help war-victims and refugees in the World War II. </span></font><br><br><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: bold; line-height: normal;">Meeting place Caritas (Counselling)</span><br><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Open: Monday, Wednesday, Friday 9:00 – 14:00</span></font><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Blekingegatan 28 A Stockholm</span></font><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">T-bana: Skanstull (exit Allhelgonagatan)</span></font><br><font face="Arial, Verdana"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Telephone: 08 – 462 00 30</span></font><br><br><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br>', 'Support to refugees, undocumented migrants and asylum seekers.<br>', 'Caritas Sweden offers individual support for people in vulnerable situations - refugees, undocumented migrants and asylum seekers. Visit them or call them at 020 462 664 to get help. <div><br></div>', 'http://www.caritas.se/', 'caritas@caritas.se', 'en', 7, 1, '2015-10-14 14:32:42'),
(41, 0, 'Fryshuset', 'logo_1435477505906.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/fryshusetsaktiviteterensamkommande?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Fryshuset - Activities for unaccompanied minors</span><div><br></div><div>A high number of young refugees arrive in Sweden on their own, without any accompanying grown-ups to support them. Fryshuset offers you, who are one of these young people, different activities related to sports, music, dance and more. They give you a chance to meet other young people who share the same interests! <br><br>Fryshuset’s room Fryschillet is open Wednesdays between 15:00-20:00. If you do not want to take part of the activities you are welcome to just hang out, listen to music, meet new friends and play games. <br><br>You can join <a href="http://ensamkommande.fryshuset.se/aktiviteter-2/">the following activities</a> for free:<br>•	Basketball, Wednesdays 18:45-19:45.<br>•	Earn-a-bike, Wednesdays 16:00-20:00.<br>•	Guitar Course, starting November 25, 18:00-19:00.<br>•	Doing homework, Wednesdays 17:00-18:00.<br>•	Dance classes at start of December.<br>•	Spontaneous football, Thursdays 19:00-21:00 at Röda Banan. <br>•	Stockholm Skatepark Wednesdays 16:00-18:00.<br><br>The first Wednesday of every month they go on trips around Stockholm. The trips can be anything from going to a museum, to the cinema or bowling. What you do is decided on Wednesday the week before!</div><div><br></div><div>Contact them on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/fryshusetsaktiviteterensamkommande?fref=ts">Facebook</a> or <a href="http://ensamkommande.fryshuset.se/aktiviteter-2/">through their website.</a><br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">About Fryshuset<br></span>Fryshuset is a place packed with all kinds of creative and constructive activities for young people in Stockholm. Young people mix with grown-ups in order to participate, contribute and learn. Fryshuset is a meeting place where people share and develop passionate interests, social commitments, sports, entertainment, culture and innovative educational programs.<br><br>Fryshuset is a non-profit organisation and it is not politically or religiously associated. To read more about all of its activities: <a href="http://fryshuset.se/in-english">http://fryshuset.se/in-english</a>/<br></div>', 'Activities for young people in Stockholm.', '<div>Fryshuset is a non-profit organisation for young people. It creates meeting places where young people are seen, heard and where they count. Find and develop your passions together with other young people!</div><div><br></div>', 'http://ensamkommande.fryshuset.se/vi-erbjuder/aktiviteter/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-11-21 16:05:25'),
(42, 0, 'Individuell Människohjälp Stockholm', 'logo_1449656842915.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/manniskohjalp', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><font size="3" style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></font></div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Individuell Människohjälp</span><br><div>Individuell Människohjälp Stockholm (IM) has a number of integration projects. It creates opportunities for interaction between new and established Swedes. In Stockholm it has an active local group and an office at Södermalm that is used as their meeting place. <br><br>The following projects are organized by Individuell Människohjälp:<br><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Duo Stockholm</span> - matches new and established Swedes.&nbsp;</li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Move it </span>- activities for minors, read more below!&nbsp;</li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Language cafe&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Homework assistance</span></li></ul><br><font size="3" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Duo Stockholm</span></font><br>Duo Stockholm wants new and established Swedes to meet. Duo Stockholm is about social contact where both parts are interested in meeting each other. <br><br>As a newcomer you get the opportunity to get to know a person who can answer your questions about the Swedish Society, who you can practice your Swedish with and who hopefully will become your friend. Both parts will definitely get new experiences and maybe new contacts. <br><br><span style="font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">Who can join Duo Stockholm? </span><br>Newcomers who can communicate a bit in Swedish and wants to improve - you have a residence permit and are 18  years. <br><br>Etablished Swedes with good knowledge of the Swedish language, Swedish society and are of 18  years. <br><br>Example of things you could do: <br>Go for a walk, go to a sport event, visit a museum, visit a parktheater, have a picnic, bake, go for a coffee etc. <br><br>Do you want to join or do you have any questions? Please contact them at: <br><br>Jonathan Österlund 0704-100318<br>Jonathan.osterlund@manniskohjalp.se<br><br>Annika Rosbring 08-50835480<br>annika.rosbring@stockholm.se<br>http://manniskohjalp.se/projekt/duo-stockholm<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;"><font size="3">Move it </font></span><br>IM gathers unaccompanied minors and organises activities where you can find new friends, practice Swedish, get to know the area you live in and find a hobby to do on your free time. Their goal is for unaccompanied minors to find a hobby they want to continue with.  <br><br>Visit their <a href="https://www.facebook.com/moveitsthlm?fref=nf" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">Facebook</a> for more information! Or their <a href="http://manniskohjalp.se/projekt/move-it-0" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">Website link</a><br><br> <br><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;"><font size="3">Språkfika/Language café</font></span> Practice your Swedish over a cup of coffee (Click on this:<a href="http://stanfornya.se/Group/2" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">&nbsp;</a><a href="http://stanfornya.se/Group/8" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">link</a>) <br><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;"><font size="3"><br>Homework Assistance</font></span> - get help with your homework (see separate links for): <br><a href="http://stanfornya.se/Group/10" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">Hässelby</a><br><a href="http://stanfornya.se/Group/9" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">Tensta</a><br><a href="http://stanfornya.se/Group/14" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">Rågsved</a><br><br><br>Visit their <a href="http://manniskohjalp.se/projekt/sverige/stockholm" style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;">website</a>!<br><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div></div>', 'A wide range of integration projects in the Stockholm area!<br>', 'IM Stockholm arranges meetings between new and established Swedes, activities for unaccompanied minors, homework assistance and language cafés.<div><br></div>', 'http://manniskohjalp.se/projekt/sverige/stockholm', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-09 12:27:22'),
(43, 0, 'Tamam Stockholm', 'logo_1441367449505.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/tamam.stockholm', '<div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tamam Stockholm – Friendship without borders<br></span><br>Tamam Stockholm works with and for children, teenagers and young adults to spread happiness, friendship and lots of love. They create new meeting places, organise meaningful sparetime activities and strive to give everyone the same opportunities in school as well as encouraging young people''s engagement in society. <br><br>They particularly welcome you who are a child or young person and newly arrived in Sweden, but they want to create opportunities for friendship between all children and youth - no matter background!<br><br>Examples of activities that Tamam Stockholm arrange:<br><ul style="font-weight: normal;"><li>Homework assistance</li><li>Sparetime activities (such as climbing every second week)</li></ul><br>For more information or to sign up for their activites: Ask your place of residence to contact them, follow them on Facebook, join their <a href="http://www.facebook.com/tamam.stockholm" style="font-weight: normal;">Facebook group</a> for activities or email them and they will put you in our mailing list!</div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">About Tamam</span></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Tamam is a non-profit and politically and religiously independent organisation working with children, teenagers and young adults. Tamam’s motto is “friendship without borders”, they want to break down the barriers that prevent young people with different backgrounds to get to know each other and become friends. Friendship cannot be forced - but you can create the prerequisites!&nbsp;</div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Read more:&nbsp;</span></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Tamam: <a href="http://www.tamam.se">http://www.tamam.se</a></div>Tamam Stockholm:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.tamam.se/blog/om-tamam/tamam-stockholm/" style="font-weight: normal;">http://www.tamam.se/blog/om-tamam/tamam-stockholm/</a><div style="font-weight: normal;"><div style="font-weight: normal;">Facebook:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/tamam.stockholm">https://www.facebook.com/tamam.stockholm</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div></div>', 'Friendship without borders - for children, teenagers and young adults', 'Tamam works with children, teenagers and young adults, particularly you who are new in Sweden. They want to create opportunities for friendship between all children and youth - no matter the background.<br>', 'http://www.tamam.se/blog/om-tamam/tamam-stockholm/', 'stockholm@tamam.se', 'en', 23, 1, '2015-09-29 16:24:58'),
(44, 0, 'Rådgivningsbyrån', 'logo_1441367338248.png', '', '<span style="font-weight: bold;">The Swedish Refugee Advice Center</span><br>Rådgivningsbyrån (The Swedish Refugee Advice Center) is a non-governmental organization that provides refugees and asylum seekers with professional legal assistance. The Swedish Refugee Advice Center is supported by a number of NGOs. Current members are Caritas, Save the Children, The Swedish Free Church Council, the Church of Sweden and Stockholms episcopate.&nbsp;<div>&nbsp; <br>They offer free legal advice on matters related to:</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>The asylum process</li><li>Family reunification</li><li>Swedish citizenship</li></ul></div><div>And/or anything else concerning the Swedish Aliens Act and international conventions.&nbsp;</div><div><br>For legal advice please call their telephone advice line; tel. 0200 - 88 00 66 Monday - Wednesday, 9.00 am - 11.00 am. If you have been appointed a legal counsel (offentligt biträde), kindly be referred to your counsel for information on your case. <br> <br>For legal advice, a summary of your case and relevant documents are required. There may be a waiting time due to their workload. Interpretation service is not provided.<br><br></div><div>Documents that they require:</div><div><ul><li>All decisions from The Migration Agency (Migrationsverket), The Migration Court (migrationsdomstolen) and The Migration Court of Appeal (Migrationsöverdomstolen)</li><li>Protocols from asylum investigations</li><li>The petitions from your legal representative</li><li>Any other appeals that have been made in your case</li></ul>If you do not have all of the documents you can obtain them from the Migration Agency or your legal counsel. They cannot review your case until all documents have been submitted. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Address:</span><br>Rådgivningsbyrån för asylsökande och flyktingar<br>Gyllenstiernsgatan 14<br>115 26 Stockholm<br>Telephone advice line: 0200-88 00 66, Monday - Wednesday 9.00 am -11.00 am.<br></div><div><br></div><div>Website:&nbsp;<a href="http://sweref.org/">http://sweref.org/</a>&nbsp;(where you also can find specific information for asylum-seeking women and children in different languages etc.)<br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br></div>', 'The Swedish Refugee Advice Center', 'Free legal advice on matters related to the asylum process, family reunification, Swedish citizenship, the Swedish Aliens Act and international conventions.&nbsp;', 'http://sweref.org/default.aspx', '', 'en', 24, 1, '2015-09-29 16:23:31'),
(45, 0, 'Sociala Missionen', 'logo_1435928105586.png', '', 'Sociala Missionen works with migration and socio-political issues at society and individual level. It offers information, help with contacts, legal and psychosocial support to asylum seekers and others.<br><br>•                          Asylum issues<br><br>•                          Family reunification<br><br>•                          Family issues<br><br>•                          Welfare and self provision issues<br><br>•                          Support in contact with authorities<br><br>•                          Elder issues<br><br>•                          Discrimination issues<br><br>•                          Integration issues<br><br>Sociala Missionen is a non-profit diaconal and social association. It started 1917 and has a great experience in working with questions regarding migration and sociopolitical issues.<br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Sociala Missionen.<br><br></span><div style="font-style: normal;">Their service is free of charge. Visit&nbsp;<a href="http://socialamissionen.se">http://socialamissionen.se</a>&nbsp;for information in Swedish or email them your questions at: info@socialamissionen.se.</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;"></span></div>', '<div>Social and diaconal association that offers free councelling to asylum seekers refugees with residence permit and other groups.</div>', 'Social and diaconal association that offers free councelling to asylum seekers refugees with residence permit and other groups.<div><br></div>', 'http://socialamissionen.se', 'info@socialamissionen.se', 'en', 18, 1, '2015-11-11 11:59:04'),
