(55, 0, 'Ensamkommandes Förbund Stockholm', 'logo_1441364347780.jpg', ' https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ensamkommandes-f��rbund-Stockholm/948465175178027?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Ensamkommandes förbund Stockholm</span></div>Ensamkommandes förbund Stockholm (Unaccompanied Minors’ Association Stockholm) is open to you who are 15-30 years of age and/or slightly younger. They arrange activities such as language training, dancing, music, theatre, sports, spare time activities and others that are suitable for the younger children of the association. They welcome all youth irregardless of ethnic background, gender or nationality.&nbsp;<div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br>Ensamkommandes förbund meets at <a href="https://www.google.se/maps/place/ABF Komvux/@59.3388249,18.0599197,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xe94f991824adac98">ABF Stockholm</a>. They offer:<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Math for beginners</span> Mondays 18-19:30<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Math for year 9 and up</span> Tuesdays 18-19:30<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">English</span> Fridays 18-19:30<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">English</span> Saturdays 16:30-18:00<br><br>Take the subway to Hötorget (green line) and walk 5 minutes to Sveavägen 41<br><br>Find them on Facebook:  <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/ensamkommandesforbundstockholm/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/ensamkommandesforbundstockholm/ </a><br><br>Or: <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ensamkommandes-f��rbund-Stockholm/948465175178027?fref=ts">https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ensamkommandes-f��rbund-Stockholm/948465175178027?fref=ts</a><br><br>Their website: <a href="http://ensamkommandesforbund.se/">http://ensamkommandesforbund.se/</a></div><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'Activities for unaccompanied minors 15-30 years of age', 'Association for unaccompanied minors that arrange activities such as language training, homework assistance, dancing, music, theatre, sports, spare time activities.<div><br></div>', 'http://ensamkommandesforbund.se/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-12-11 18:42:44'),
(56, 0, 'Juventas Sisters ', 'logo_1441362897257.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/juventas.systrar.5?fref=nf', '<span class="_5yl5" data-reactid=".ch.1:$mid=11444397784681=283b01b705713526469.2:0.0.0.0.0"><span data-reactid=".ch.1:$mid=11444397784681=283b01b705713526469.2:0.0.0.0.0.0">Juventas Sisters is an organisation that offers young girls, who are new in Sweden, the chance of getting a big sister. nn<br><br>A big sister is an older girl who is there for you to listen, support and encourage you! You meet to talk and/or to do an activity you both want to do.n<br><br>nIf you are 13-21 years old and live in Södertälje you can get a big sister from Juventas Sisters. You can meet your sister twice a month over a period of 10 months. You can try out new activities, go to the cinema, talk or anything you both feel like doing. <br>A big sister is free of charge.<br><br>If you want a big sister, send an email to, or call Juventas Sisters at: nEmail: info@juventassystrar.senTelephone: 08-550 680 60nnThe organisation Juventas Sisters also have other ways of supporting young girls. <br><br>On Tuesday evenings 18:30-21:00 you can chat with volunteers from the organisation. In the chat room you are free to ask anything you want to – no thoughts, topics or problems are too big, too small or too strange! <a href="http://www.juventassystrar.se/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/chatta.html">Click here</a> to come to the chatroom. nn<br><br>You can also contact them via their <a href="https://www.facebook.com/juventas.systrar.5?fref=ts">Facebook pagenn</a><br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></span></span><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; text-align: right;">هل تحتاجين لاخت كبيرة؟</div><div style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><br></span></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">هل انت شابة ما بين ال 13 و 21 عاما و مقيمة في السويد لمدة سنة؟</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">هل تحتاجين شخصا تتكلمين معه,  شخصا يسمعك؟ هل تشعرين بالوحدة بالرغم من وجود اناس حولك؟</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">لدينا مشروع جديد اسمه الاخوات الطيبات حيث يمكنك الحصول على اخت كبيرة. الاخت الكبيرة هي شابة بالغة و ستقوم بدور اخت كبيرة حيث انها سوف تشجعكي,</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">تسمعكي و تعضدكي. انت و الاخت الكبيرة تلتقون مرتين في الشهر للكلام , الذهاب الى السينما و غيرها من نشاطات.</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">انتم تقررون ما تفعلون عندما تلتقون. هذا الشي مجاني و اختك الكبيرة ستكون حافضة اسرارك و ستتكلم العربية, السريانية</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">و نحن بدورنا سنقوم مساعدتك على التعرف بالاخت المناسبة</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">08-550 680 60 اتصلي بنا على الرقم التالي</div></span><div style="text-align: right;"><br></div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px;"><div style="text-align: right;">info@juventassystrar.se او راسلينا على</div></span></div><div style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; line-height: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-family: Arial, Verdana; font-size: 12px; font-style: italic;">Text written by&nbsp;Juventas Systrar.</span></div>', '<style>n<!--n /* Font Definitions */n@font-facen	{font-family:"ＭＳ 明朝";n	mso-font-charset:78;n	mso-generic-font-family:auto;n	mso-font-pitch:variable;n	mso-font-signature:1 134676480 16 0 131072 0;}n@font-facen	{font-family:"ＭＳ 明朝";n	mso-font-charset:78;n	mso-generic-font-family:auto;n	mso-font-pitch:variable;n	mso-font-signature:1 134676480 16 0 131072 0;}n@font-facen	{font-family:Cambria;n	panose-1:2 4 5 3 5 4 6 3 2 4;n	mso-font-charset:0;n	mso-generic-font-family:auto;n	mso-font-pitch:variable;n	mso-font-signature:-536870145 1073743103 0 0 415 0;}n /* Style Definitions */np.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormaln	{mso-style-unhide:no;n	mso-style-qformat:yes;n	mso-style-parent:"";n	margin:0cm;n	margin-bottom:.0001pt;n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;n	font-size:12.0pt;n	font-family:Cambria;n	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria;n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;n	mso-fareast-font-family:"ＭＳ 明朝";n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;n	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria;n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;n	mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}n.MsoChpDefaultn	{mso-style-type:export-only;n	mso-default-props:yes;n	font-family:Cambria;n	mso-ascii-font-family:Cambria;n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;n	mso-fareast-font-family:"ＭＳ 明朝";n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;n	mso-hansi-font-family:Cambria;n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;n	mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";n	mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}n@page WordSection1n	{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;n	margin:70.85pt 70.85pt 70.85pt 70.85pt;n	mso-header-margin:36.0pt;n	mso-footer-margin:36.0pt;n	mso-paper-source:0;}ndiv.WordSection1n	{page:WordSection1;}n-->n</style>Sisterhood for young girls in Södertälje.', 'If you are a young girl who recently arrived in Sweden, Juventas Sisters can give you a big sister!<br><div><br></div>', 'http://www.juventassystrar.se/stod-och-pepp/storasyster/', 'info@juventassystrar.se', 'en', 14, 1, '2015-10-09 16:47:19'),
(57, 0, 'FARR', 'logo_1441371829023.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/flykting?fref=nf', '<div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div>FARR, the Swedish Network of Refugee Support Groups, is a non-profit organisation. It consists of voluntary groups and individual members around the country. One of FARR''s most important tasks is to provide advice and support to you as an asylum seeker.	<div style="font-style: normal;">&nbsp;			<br>FARR produces <a href="http://www.farr.se/sv/aktuellt-a-press/notiser/1123-farrs-good-advice-updated-in-6-languages">Good Advice</a> (Full name: <span style="font-style: italic;">Good Advice For Asylum Seekers in Sweden</span>), which is a booklet that informs you as an asylum seeker of your rights and what you can do to affect the outcome of your case. It is available in six different languages (Swedish, Arabic, Spanish, Farsi, Russian, English).&nbsp;</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br>You can find the 	booklet here: <a href="http://www.farr.se/sv/aktuellt-a-press/notiser/1123-farrs-good-advice-updated-in-6-languages">http://www.farr.se/sv/aktuellt-a-press/notiser/1123-farrs-good-advice-updated-in-6-languages	</a></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br>Note: As a voluntary organisation, FARR cannot change the law or decide how it should be interpreted. Through Good Advice they want to inform you of your rights and what you can do to affect the outcome of your case.</div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;">Visit their website (mainly in Swedish):&nbsp;<a href="http://www.far.se">http://www.farr.se</a></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span></div>', 'A network of refugee support groups. Information for asylum seekers.', 'FARR, the Swedish Network of Refugee Support Groups, provides advice and support to you as an asylum seeker through the Good Advice booklet', 'http://www.far.se', '', 'en', 22, 1, '2015-09-29 16:18:52'),
(60, 0, 'Red Cross', 'logo_1441793599464.jpg', '', 'The Red Cross provides support, information and care for migrants and refugees in Sweden. Read more about the support you can below: <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Undocumented migrants</span><br>•	Information and help to those who live undocumented in Sweden (not a Swedish citizen and live in the country without permission). <br>•	Meeting place on Hornsgatan 54 in Stockholm every Tuesday 14:30 - for legal and social support. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">War and torture injuries</span><br>•	Treatment centre for asylum seekers, undocumented migrants or people with residence permits in Sweden whom have been victims of torture or difficult war experiences. Located in Stockholm.<br>•	Support telephone: 020-41 50 00 Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday 9:30-12:00. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Support for asylum seekers</span><br>•	Information, advice and assistance to asylum seekers. Information about the asylum process, counselling in asylum cases (specifically torture and gender-related matters), support in the return process.<br>•	Support telephone: 020-41 50 00 Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday 9:30-12:00. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Support for unaccompanied children and young people</span><br>•	For asylum seekers, undocumented migrants or people with residence permits in Sweden whom are unaccompanied minors or youth (below 18 years old). <br>•	<a href="http://rkuf.se/vad-vi-gor/kompisgrupper/">Friendship-groups </a><br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Red Cross Messages</span><br>•	For those who want to contact a relative in an area affected by war, conflict or natural disaster, or is a prisoner of war. <a href="â¢ http://www.redcross.se/detta-gor-vi/stod-till-migranter/rodakorsmeddelanden/">See their website. </a><br><br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Tracing of relatives</span><br>•	For those who need help to find a missing family member.<br>•	Support telephone: 020-41 50 00 Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday 9:30-12:00. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Family reunification</span><br>•	Information about and help with government and organisation contacts, support, practical help and/or financial support regarding family reunification. <br>•	Support telephone: 020-41 50 00 Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday 9:30-12:00. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Certificate of captivity</span><br>•	For those who need proof (a certificate) of imprisonment or detainment in another country. Note: you can only get a certificate of captivity if the International Red Cross Committee has visited and registered you. <br>•	Support telephone: 020-41 50 00 Tuesday/Wednesday/Thursday 9:30-12:00. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Practice your Swedish </span><br>•	Free Swedish language training for asylum seekers, undocumented migrants and those who have received their residence permits.  See <a href="http://stanfornya.se/Events">calendar</a> and <a href="http://stanfornya.se/Groups">meeting places </a>for more information.<br>• Or see <a href="â¢ Free Swedish language training for asylum seekers, undocumented migrants and those who have received their residence permits. See calendar and meeting places for more information.">their map</a> and find the meeting place closest to you!<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Kompis Sverige (Buddy Sweden)</span><br>•	A project that matches newcomers and established Swedes. <a href="http://stanfornya.se/Organization/29">Click here</a> to read more. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Short information about the Red Cross: </span><br>Red Cross promotes a humane and legally secure refugee policy and understanding of people displaced, both in Sweden and internationally. They are engaged in most parts of the refugee and integration policies; counselling on the asylum process, family reunification, the exercise of the Swedish language and return.<br>Red Cross defends asylum seekers and refugees, human rights, notably the right to asylum and the right to live with their family. Every year they help a few thousand people reunited in Sweden.<br><br>For people who are victims of war and torture injuries, they have the treatment centre and for asylum seekers and undocumented they brokering of care.<br><br>Access to basic health care is a human right. In Sweden there are still vulnerable people and groups that do not have full access to it; undocumented and war and torture injuries are examples of people for whom the Red Cross have their own activities to meet these needs.<br><br><span style="font-style: italic;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</span><br>', 'Help and support for refugees, asylum seekers, undocumented, minors etc<br>', 'Help and support for refugees, asylum seekers, undocumented, minors etc', 'http://www.redcross.se/detta-gor-vi/stod-till-migranter/', '', 'en', 1, 1, '2015-09-29 16:18:26'),
