(65, 0, 'KomHIT - DART', 'logo_1442847709370.png', '', '<div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="line-height: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">KomHIT - DART</span></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">Today, people are fleeing to Sweden. Many of them are children, and many come alone. In meeting Swedish society, communication difficulties arise because we do not speak the same language. It can also be difficult to put into words what we have experienced. The images that you find on <a href="www.kom-hit.se/flykting">www.kom-hit.se/flykting</a> can be used as support in communication with others.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br>Images can be helpful when the language is not sufficient. Images can serve as a bridge between to languages. They make it easier to understand others and express oneself.  The images on <a href="www.kom-hit.se/flykting">www.kom-hit.se/flykting</a> are designed to make it easier for children to talk about fleeing difficult circumstances. <br><br>The material can be downloaded in Swedish, English and Arabic. <br><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">For conversations about the refugee experience – go here: <br><ul><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_resan_svenska.pdf">Swedish</a></li><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_resan_engelska.pdf">English</a></li><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_resan_arabiska.pdf">Arabic</a></li></ul>For conversations about everyday matters – go here: </div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><ul><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_vardagen_svenska.pdf">Swedish</a></li><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_vardagen_engelska.pdf">English</a></li><li><a href="http://kom-hit.se/flykting/pdf/Bildkarta_flyktingar_om_vardagen_arabiska.pdf">Arabic</a></li></ul></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">KomHIT is also a national web resource in which staff and parents can download communication support materials (images) for children in contact with pediatric or dental services. At <a href="www.bildstod.se">www.bildstod.se</a>, you can register an account and download, or create, communication support materials for a wide range of situations.</div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">About KomHIT</div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;">The purpose of KomHIT is to ensure children’s rights to communication and allow for their activity and participation during hospital or dental visits.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-weight: normal; line-height: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">KomHIT is a project by Arvsfonden (the Swedish Inheritance Fund). Collaborators are DART (organised under the Department of Neurology, Psychiatry and Habilitation of Sahlgrenska University, Gothenburg, Sweden), different units of child health care and dental care in the region of Västra Götaland, FUB in Lerum, DHB Västra, and the&nbsp;Autism and Asperger Association in Gothenburg and Southern Bohuslän.&nbsp;</div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Read more (in Swedish): <a href="http://www.kom-hit.se">www.kom-hit.se</a></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Text written by Stan för nyanlända.</div>', 'Communication support materials (images) for children refugees.', 'Download communication support materials (images) to be used by children in contact with medical and dental services, or for conversations about the refugee experience.<div><br></div>', 'http://www.kom-hit.se/flykting/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-11-21 15:59:58'),
