(77, 0, 'Meet My City', 'logo_1444246799823.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/Meetmycitynow/timeline', '<div><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span></div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Meet My City&nbsp;</span><div style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-style: normal;">Meet My City is a new integration project found in Stockholm, Vienna, Gdansk, Vilnius, Perm, Moscow, Sankt Petersburg and Berlin. <br><br>The project is for you who have recently migrated to Sweden. It matches you with a person who lives in your city and who can give you a personalized guided tour of his or her favourite part of town. After you sign up, you get an email with suggestions of dates, locations and what to do!<br><br>The idea is simple. People from different backgrounds meet. They show each other the hometown where they live. It is a personalised guided tour.<br><br>The project aims to create a platform to build bridges between migrants and local communities. <br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">About</span></div><div style="font-style: normal;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"><br></span>The people behind the project believe that a person who has migrated becomes a local when bonds are tied to the people and the city where he or she lives. If you have your own sweet spots in the area where you live, a network of friends and perhaps an involvement in local events – you are a part of the society. <br><br>Visit their website to read more and sign up!<br><br><a href="http://www.meetmycity.org">www.meetmycity.org</a><br></div>', 'Personalized guided tours by locals for newcomers in Stockholm!', 'The idea behind Meet My City is simple. People from different backgrounds meet. They show each other the hometown where they live. It is a personalized guided tour.<br><div><br></div>', 'http://www.meetmycity.org', '', 'en', 5, 1, '2015-10-08 21:18:47'),
(80, 0, 'I am not a refugee.', 'logo_1444394286238.png', 'https://www.facebook.com/iamnotarefugee?fref=ts', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">I am not a refugee.</span></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div>I am not a refugee was created by a group of friends from Sweden, Brazil, Russia, Canada and Denmark. <div><br></div><div>It is a site designed to help refugees find work appropriate to their skills. <br><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">They write: You fought for safety, now we will help you fight for a job. Fill in the blanks and together we will continue to write your story where it left off.</div></div><div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div style="font-weight: normal;">Visit their website: www.iamnotarefugee.com.</div>', 'A site designed to help refugees find work appropriate to their skills.', 'I am not a refugee. is a site designed to help refugees find work appropriate to their skills.<br><div><br></div>', 'http://www.iamnotarefugee.com', '', 'en', 6, 1, '2015-10-11 14:22:00'),
(81, 0, 'Folkuniversitetet', 'logo_1445328143749.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/folkuniversitetetstockholm', 'Folkuniversitetet offers free Swedish courses. The courses are free of charge, but in order to register you must have a LMA number, which you must provide when registering. You must have your LMA card with you at the first lesson. Please note that you cannot take these courses if you have obtained a residence permit, unless you still live in a asylum accommodation.  <br><br>To enroll, click t<a href="http://www.folkuniversitetet.com/Kurser--Utbildningar/Sprakkurser/Svenska_Swedish/svenska-for-asylsokande/?page=1#kurslista">his link</a>, and choose you city in order to find out what Swedish courses there are near your!', 'Free Swedish courses for asylum-seekers<br>', 'Free Swedish courses for asylum-seekers. <br>', 'http://www.folkuniversitetet.com/Kurser--Utbildningar/Sprakkurser/Svenska_Swedish/svenska-for-asylsokande/?page=1#kurslista', 'direkt@folkuniversitetet.se', 'en', 9, 1, '2015-10-20 11:02:41'),
(82, 0, 'Refunite', 'logo_1446560166296.jpg', 'https://www.facebook.com/refunite/timeline', '<div style="font-weight: normal;"><br></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">Refunite</span></div>Refunite is a non-profit organisation that allows refugees so search for their missing family members. Using technology, they have created a user friendly, online global database of over 405 000 profiles. Users can therefore on their own hand search through the database to find their missing loved ones. <br><br>They write: &nbsp;<div>"Everyone has the right to know where their family is. This belief is at the core of REFUNITE, a nonprofit tech organization whose mission is to reconnect refugee families across the globe with missing loved ones. <br><br>When families are separated, we put them back in touch. We empower refugees and displaced people to take the search for missing loved ones into their own hands, whether through a mobile phone, a computer or one of our free help lines. Today, there are millions of forcibly displaced people worldwide, a large percentage of whom have lost contact with family members or friends in their escape from disasters, persecutions, or conflicts. REFUNITE’s long-standing partnerships with Ericsson, mobile network operators and the United Nations have allowed us to collaborate on the pervasive problem of family separation among forcibly displaced populations, to witness the effects of these separations, and to refine their approach to reconnect loved ones."<br><br>Visit their <a href="https://refunite.org/" style="font-weight: normal;">website</a>!<br><br></div>', 'Search for missing family members.<br>', 'Are you looking for missing family members or friends? Refugees United is a free online family tracing tool that provides refugees and refugee agencies alike with a means to instantly engage in the process of family tracing through web and mobile phones.<br><div><br></div>', 'https://refunite.org/', '', 'en', 0, 1, '2015-11-21 16:03:32');


